E. COLI, SECONDARY INFECTION - UK (SCOTLAND)
============================================
Date: Tue, 27 May 1997 08:44:21 -0400
From: "Robert A. LaBudde" <ral@lcfltd.com>
via: FSNET (Univ. Guelph, Doug Powell)
"E.COLI AT HOSPITAL THAT TREATED KILLER OUTBREAK"
May 26, 1997, PA News, Louisa Buller
A hospital in Scotland, The Falkirk and District Royal Infirmary, has 12
confirmed cases of E. coli O157:H7 among its elderly patients and staff.A
statement issued by Central Scotland Healthcare NHS Trust, which manages
the three wards involved in the outbreak, was quoted as stating that "All
the residents affected are elderly and frail, but are currently not causing
any additional clinical concern."
The source of the infection, according to this story, is not yet known.
